claim.claim-text:
1. A method for predicting the coefficient of restitution of a golf club, the method comprising: 
attaching a vibration sensor to a face of the golf club; 
impacting the attached vibration sensor with an excitation device to generate vibrations in the face; 
transmitting the force of excitation from the excitation device and the vibrations measured by the vibration sensor to an analyzer to generate frequency domain data for the golf club; 
transforming the frequency domain data for the golf club into a transfer function for the golf club; and 
inputting a golf ball model for a specific golf ball into the transfer function and an impact speed in order to generate a predicted COR for the golf club at the impact speed with the specific golf ball.

6. The method according to claim 1 wherein transforming the frequency domain data comprises: 
generating a graph of the frequency; 
analyzing the phase of the motion of the face of the golf club; 
selecting a frequency band to minimize noise; and 
calculating the transfer function.

13. The system according to claim 10 wherein the calculating means comprises: 
means for generating frequency domain data from the vibrations of the face of the golf club; 
means for generating a graph of the frequency from the frequency domain data; 
means for analyzing the phase of the motion of the face of the golf club; 
means for selecting a frequency band to minimize noise; and 
means for calculating a transfer function.

15. A method for predicting the coefficient of restitution of a golf club head, the method comprising: 
attaching a vibration sensor to a face of the golf club head; 
impacting the attached vibration sensor with an impact device to generate vibrations in the face; 
transmitting the force of impact from the impact device and the vibrations measured by the vibration sensor to an analyzer to generate frequency domain data for the golf club head; 
transforming the frequency domain data for the golf club head into a transfer function for the golf club head; and 
inputting a golf ball model for a specific golf ball into the transfer function and an impact speed in order to generate a predicted COR for the golf club head at the impact speed with the specific golf ball.

16. The method according to claim 15 wherein transforming the frequency domain data comprises: 
generating a graph of the frequency; 
analyzing the phase of the motion of the face of the golf club head; 
selecting a frequency band to minimize noise; and 
calculating the transfer function.

19. A method for predicting the coefficient of restitution of a golf club, the method comprising: 
attaching a vibration sensor to a face of the golf club; 
exciting the attached vibration sensor with an excitation device to generate vibrations in the face; 
transmitting the force of excitation from the excitation device and the vibrations measured by the vibration sensor to an analyzer to generate time domain data for the golf club; 
transforming the time domain data for the golf club into a state-space representation of the golf club; and 
inputting a golf ball model for a specific golf ball into the transfer function and an impact speed in order to generate a predicted COR for the golf club at the specified impact speed with the specific golf ball.
